reviews.text:
Let me praise the girl that serves us the food and taking food order from us. She is very very professional and polite, love her attitude toward the customer. There for service for sure 5 stars.

Food 5 stars, i will come back to try again.
Their dishes is authentic and serve and cook by Thai. Compare to Nakhon is cheaper and same or better standard.(my opinion)
Portion is great.

Total 30+ for 2 person. Each pay 16?
Pandang Chicken 4.5 stars, authentic
Omlette egg 4.7stars,  is Authentic and addictive, we should have order bigger portion.
Raw Prawn, yes rawww, 5stars, very fresh and they handle it well. Love it. And the sauce for it.
Clear Tom Yum Soup, 4.7 stars soup taste, seafood taste and all seasoning are just nice. Perfect
Pineapple fried rice, great amount of seafood and blend well. 4.5 stars

Atmosphere is good, is a coffee shop. Again very cheap, i will be back for it.

Absolutely amazing place PLEASE DON'T EVER CLOSE!!!

Their food is really tasty and reasonably priced - love the Tom yum and fried rice and special shout out to the raw prawn salad for always being so fresh.

Lady boss and her daughter are so lovely and polite. It's always a joy patronizing them!

Your friendly neighborhood Thai food stall.

Friendly service and good value, managed by Thai people so it can be as spicy and authentic as you like it to be.

If you have a favorite dish that's not on their menu try asking them if they can make it!

Extremely impressed with how affordable it was for high quality authentic Thai food in a coffee shop! Portions were generous too. Dishes are prepared by a Thai family (itâ€™s a family business). Definitely deserve much more recognition and I wish them a successful business
Authentic Thai food with great service from the family! They were from Diandin Leluk Din at Golden Mile! We spent $30 for family of four.
